Police are looking for a man seen leaving a house shortly before it was gutted in a fire.Firefighters dealt with the blaze at about 06:10 BST in Windsor Street, New Brighton, Wirral.Merseyside Police said nobody was in the house when the fire, which caused "extensive damage", broke out.A joint investigation into its cause is being carried out by Merseyside Fire and Rescue Service and Merseyside Police.
Det Insp Sean Cloherty said: "The investigation is in the early stages as we carry out enquiries in the area. "I am particularly keen to trace and speak with a male who was seen on Windsor Street approximately 04:00 and I would urge anyone with information as to his identity to contact us."He also appealed for anyone with CCTV, doorbell or dashcam footage to contact police.
